      "writtenOn": "2021-01-21T01:17:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My reasoning is that luci.bucket is a subclass of luci.realm (it is a realm plus some additional thing). `extends` and `bindings` are both properties of luci.realm, thus luci.bucket inherits and exposes them too.\n\nAlso you can totally say:\n\n  luci.bucket(name \u003d \"a\")\n  luci.bucket(name \u003d \"b\", extends \u003d \"a\")\n\nBecause a bucket is a realm. I felt that renaming `extends` into something else will be more confusing than not.\n\nRe `acls`: they\u0027ll go away eventually (will be replaced by `bindings`).",
      "parentUuid": "00feba75_e95ab3e3",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1284,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 1284,
        "endChar": 11
